<plot>In this African Folktale, the Sun (in a round, orange mask) and the Moon (in a purple, rhombus-shaped mask) once lived as husband and wife in a hut on land. When they invite too many people and other creatures to a party, they are gradually pushed up from their little hut and into the sky.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?655941</url></doc>
